      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(slack): fail unconfirmed threaded deliveries",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\nSlack threaded outbound sends could report success even when Slack did not confirm delivery into the requested thread. The send layer previously exposed `threadTs` by falling back to the requested value, so the outbound adapter could not distinguish a real Slack-confirmed thread from an echoed request.\n\nThe first repair also applied that strict confirmation check to the media upload path. That was too broad because Slack media uploads legitimately preserve the requested thread through their upload flow rather than returning the same confirmation field used by text sends.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\nThis change separates requested thread fallback from Slack-confirmed thread evidence on text sends while keeping threaded media uploads on their existing delivery path. `sendMessageSlack` exposes `confirmedThreadTs` only when Slack returns `message.thread_ts`, and the outbound adapter fails a requested threaded text payload unless that confirmed value matches the target thread.\n\nThe confirmation guard is now scoped to non-media payloads. Receipts and participation tracking continue to use the best delivered thread value for existing Slack behavior.\n\n## User Impact\nWhen Slack omits or changes the destination thread for a text message, OpenClaw now surfaces a delivery failure instead of silently marking the reply as delivered to the original thread. Successful threaded Slack sends are unchanged.\n\nThreaded Slack file/media uploads keep working and are not rejected just because the text-message confirmation field is absent.\n\n## Evidence\nHead commit: `988e0fa60e50425d941bda539026ae8e6b323a66`.\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/slack/src/outbound-adapter.test.ts extensions/slack/src/send.blocks.test.ts` passed.\n- `pnpm oxfmt --check extensions/slack/src/send.ts extensions/slack/src/outbound-adapter.ts extensions/slack/src/outbound-adapter.test.ts extensions/slack/src/send.blocks.test.ts` passed.\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions:test` passed.\n- `git diff --check` passed.\n\nRegression coverage now includes:\n\n- threaded text sends fail when Slack omits the confirmed thread id;\n- successful threaded text sends continue to pass when Slack confirms the requested thread;\n- threaded media uploads preserve the requested `thread_ts` path and are not rejected by the text-send confirmation guard.\r\n",
        "branch": "fix/slack-thread-delivery-confirmation",
